<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12">
    <h3><code>ui-buttons</code></h3>
    <h3>Buttons Component</h3>
    <desc>
      The buttons component is a <i>grouping</i> of buttons that can be used in a template as either <b>block</b> or <b>inline</b> component. The examples below illustrate both styles. For more information on this component see the sections on <a href="#state-mgmt">state management</a> and <a href="#messaging">messaging</a>.
    </desc>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Block Style</h3>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-2">
    {{#ui-buttons}}
      {{ui-button title='foo'}}
      {{ui-button title='bar'}}
      {{ui-button title='baz'}}
    {{/ui-buttons}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-5 col-lg-5 monospace">
  <b>\{{#ui-buttons}}</b><br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='foo'}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='bar'}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='baz'}}<br/>
  <b>\{{/ui-buttons}}</b>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5">
    Illustrates the most basic usage of this component. Basically all you're getting here is some additional bootstrap styling which rounds the corners in a pleasing way.
  </div>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-2">
    {{#ui-buttons howMany=howMany disabled=d size=s cardinality='1:1' as |g1|}}
      {{ui-button title='foo' group=g1}}
      {{ui-button title='bar' group=g1}}
      {{ui-button title='baz' group=g1}}
    {{/ui-buttons}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-5 col-lg-5 monospace">
  <b>\{{#ui-buttons disabled=d size=s as |g1|}}</b><br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='foo' group=g1}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='bar' group=g1}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='baz' group=g1}}<br/>
  <b>\{{/ui-buttons}}</b>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5">
    Associating the button with the <code>ui-buttons</code> component is achieved by setting the <code>group</code> property to the yielded value of buttons component. This automatically takes care of item registration and allows the container to orchestrate global properties like sizing, enablement/disablement, etc.<br/>
    <p class="downer">
      {{ui-toggle-button on='enable the group' off='disable the group' value=d }}
      <br/>
      <p class="downer">
        {{ui-buttons buttons='small,normal,large' value=s size='small' cardinality='1:1'}}
      </p>

    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-2">
    {{#ui-buttons as |g2|}}
      {{ui-radio-button title='foo' group=g2}}
      {{ui-radio-button title='bar' group=g2}}
      {{ui-radio-button title='baz' group=g2}}
    {{/ui-buttons}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-5 col-lg-5 monospace">
  <b>\{{#ui-buttons as |g2|}}</b><br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-radio-button title='foo' group=g2}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-radio-button title='bar' group=g2}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-radio-button title='baz' group=g2}}<br/>
  <b>\{{/ui-buttons}}</b><br/>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5">
    Up to now we were just using the regular old <code>ui-button</code> button but more often then not when're grouping buttons we're going to want to use either a <em>radio</em> or <em>checkbox</em> styled button which contains some "state". In the case of a
    radio button, you can see that only one button at a time can be picked.
  </div>
</div>
<hr>



<br/>
<h3>Inline Style</h3>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-2">
    {{ui-buttons
      buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz'
    }}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-5 monospace">
  <b>\{{ui-buttons </b><br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz'<br/>
  }}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-6 col-lg-5">
    The basic inline syntax.<br/>

    <note class="note"><b>Note</b>:   by default the values that each button take on
      are dasherized version of the string and button type is <code>ui-button</code>.</note>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-5 col-sm-3 col-lg-3">
    {{ui-buttons
      type='radio'
      buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz'
      disabled='baz'
      moodActive='success'
      defaultValue='bar'
    }}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-lg-4 monospace">
  <b>\{{ui-buttons </b><br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz' <br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;type='radio'<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;disabled='baz'<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;moodActive='success'<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;defaultValue='bar'<br/>
  }}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-6 col-lg-5">
    A few more things to take note of:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <b>type</b> - a 'radio' or 'checkbox' are the most handy types of buttons but you must specify which type you want as the default button will be used otherwise.
      </li>
      <li><b>disabled</b> - you can set the disabled property to either a boolean which has a global effect on all the buttons or to a specific value which disables only the button which has this value</li>
    </ul>
    More on these properties later ...
  </div>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-5 col-sm-3 col-lg-3">
    {{ui-buttons
      type='radio'
      buttons=dynButtons
      size=size
      moodActive='warning'
      defaultValue='baz'
      canBeEmpty=canBeEmpty
    }}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-lg-4 monospace">
  <b>\{{ui-buttons </b><br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;buttons='{{dynButtons}}' <br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;type='radio'<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;moodActive='success'<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;defaultValue='bar'<br/>{{#if size}}
  &nbsp;&nbsp;size='{{size}}'<br/>{{/if}}{{#if canBeEmpty}}
  &nbsp;&nbsp;canBeEmpty=true<br/>{{/if}}
  <b>}}</b>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-6 col-lg-5">
    Now play around with a few parameters:
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-3">buttons</div>
      <div class="col-xs-9">
        {{text-input value=dynButtons }}
      </div>
      <br/>
      <div class="col-xs-3">Active Mood</div>
      <div class="col-xs-9">
         {{ui-buttons type='radio' value=activeButtonMood buttons='default,warning,danger'}}
      </div>
      <br/>
      <div class="col-xs-3 downer">size</div>
      <div class="col-xs-9 downer">
        {{ui-buttons buttons=sizes size='small' type='radio' value=size }}
      </div>
      <br/>
      <div class="col-xs-3 downer">canBeEmpty</div>
      <div class="col-xs-9 downer">
        {{ui-buttons
          buttons=canBeEmptyValues
          value=canBeEmpty
          size='small'
          type='radio'
          defaultValue=true
          icon=icon
          onIcon=iconActive
          offIcon=iconInactive
          canBeEmpty=false
        }}
      </div><br/>
      <div class="col-xs-3 downer">icons</div>
      <div class="col-xs-9 downer">
        {{ui-buttons
          buttons='none,both,active,inactive'
          value=iconStrategy
          size='small'
          type='radio'
          defaultValue='none'
          canBeEmpty=false
        }}
      </div><br/>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<br/>

<h3>Data Down, Actions Up</h3>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-5 col-sm-3 col-lg-3">
    {{ui-buttons
      type='radio'
      buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz'
      defaultValue='bar'
      value=listenDontTalk
      changed="changed"
    }}<br/>
    <p class="downer">value: {{listenDontTalk}}</p>  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-lg-4 monospace">
  <b>\{{ui-buttons </b><br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz' <br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;type='radio'<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;defaultValue='bar'<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;value=listenDontTalk<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;changed="changed"<br/>
  }}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-5 col-lg-5">
    We're trying to use the now accepted norm of "data down, actions up" to avoid side-effects and therefore when you use the <code>ui-buttons</code> components you can bind input values such as <i>size</i>,
  </div>
</div>


<h3 id='messaging'>Messaging API</h3>
<desc>
  <p>
    The buttons components is a wrapper around the various button types and therefore has a proscribed messaging API that is taken care of for you when using the inline style but is also managed for you if your button items pass the yielded block parameter into the button's
    <code>group</code> property.
